assess_results_desc: What do you see on your test strip?
description_positive: A POSITIVE result is indicated by the presence of a BLUE line and a PINK line. Examples of positive results are presented above. Look closely, even a faint PINK line is considered positive.
description_negative: A NEGATIVE result is indicated by the presence of a BLUE line AND NO PINK line. Examples of negative results are presented above.
description_equivocal: An INVALID result is indicated if the BLUE line does not appear, even if a PINK line appears. Examples of invalid results are presented above. If the test is invalid, a new test should be performed with a new patient sample and a new Strip.
